  "commentary": "With SPX at 6602.57 sitting just below the GEX flip at 6611 and near the massive +22.2B gamma wall at 6605, dealers are positioned to sell any push higher into that resistance zone. The PIN regime with 51.1B total GEX creates strong mean-reverting forces, while the wall break and GEX surge events suggest we just saw significant options flow that's now anchoring price action around current levels. Key levels to watch: 6605 resistance where dealer selling intensifies, 6611 flip line that changes the hedging dynamic, and 6590 support where negative gamma could amplify any breakdown.\n\nBottom line: expect price to get pinned between 6590-6610 with dealers capping upside moves.",
